    <title>Combined summary - Base AMP</title>
    <updated>2023-05-25T16:55:40.718695+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2018-November/001680.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The Lightning Network community is currently discussing the implementation of a new feature called Base AMP which would allow users to split payments across multiple paths. There are debates around the specifics of how this feature should be implemented, including proposals to use a 2-byte "number of total pieces" or an optional field on the invoice that would let the receiver wait until all funds have been received before pulling the payment. A divide and conquer algorithm has also been proposed.Discussions in the Lightning-dev mailing list revolve around signaling support for Base AMP, whether an algorithm should be specified for executing a multipath payment, and whether arbitrary merges of payment paths should be allowed. One proposal suggests using a new `multipath_merge_per_hop` type (`option_base_amp`) that indicates the payment has been split by the sender using Base AMP, and that the receiver should wait for the total intended payment before forwarding or claiming the payment.There have been debates about the reliability and simplicity of Lightning, such as endpoint-only merging versus in-route merging. The issue of fees and their impact on the network was also raised, with some suggesting that restricting merge points to ultimate payees may be a good approach to take.The email thread discusses modification made to support Base AMP in Lightning Network payments. The proposal allows arbitrary merges of paths but not arbitrary splits. The `multipath_merge_per_hop` type consists of five data elements: `short_channel_id`, `amt_to_forward`, `outgoing_cltv_value`, `intended_total_payment`, and `zeros`. The contents of this hop will be the same across all paths of the Base AMP. The `payment_hash` of the incoming HTLCs will also be the same across all paths of the Base AMP.Overall, the details of Base AMP's implementation will be determined through further discussion among the Lightning Network community.</summary>
